  <Content>The Eulogy 

Kalliope, survivor of The Sacrifice, writes of the ceremony: 

&lt;I&gt;The 32nd  anniversary of Danaan's sacrifice is upon us. The woods near Undine are restless with fear. Rat-like eyes infiltrate the night. 

Traveling bards tell me that it is the same near Pravat and Mehadi. The world is aflame for the worship of the thirty-second  anniversary of Her sacrifice. The fervor concerns me. Each day the worshippers grow more hostile to those they consider unbelievers. 

